METHODOLOGY:
This bill prohibits smoking in Hampton Beach State Park, including the RV park, and requires
the Department of Natural and Cultural Resources (DNCR) to post signage notifying the public
oftheprohibition.
The New Hampshire Department of Natural and Cultural Resources states this bill may result
in a minor decrease in State Park Fund revenue, estimated at up to $50,000 annually, due to
reduced visitation. Because the bill takes effect January 1, 2027, the Department assumes the
impact in FY 2027 would be approximately half that amount. Any costs for signage and
implementationcanbeabsorbedwithintheDepartment’sexistingbudget.
